    "en": {
      "title": "Forex fell by 51.6 percent",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Amidst the economic crisis the country is facing, there has been a massive drop in foreign exchange remittances to Sri Lanka by foreign workers in the first six months of 2022. In the period under consideration, foreign exchange has decreased to $1.6 billion, which is calculated to be a 51.6 percent decline.",
        "Foreign remittances sent by foreign workers last month stood at 274.3 million US dollars, compared to 478.4 million US dollars in the same period in 2021.",
        "Remittances by Sri Lankans abroad increased to $304 million in May from $249 million in April.",
        "But it is reported that it has fallen again in the month of June. The Central Bank reports that Sri Lankans abroad have reduced remittances due to the economic crisis in the country."
      ],
